{"id": "launch-progress", "name": "IdiamPro - Launch Progress", "rootNodeId": "lp-root", "lastModified": 1779819018832, "nodes": {"lp-root": {"id": "lp-root", "name": "Launch Progress", "content": "<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-05-21 (Gemini 3.5 Flash switch shipped)</p><p></p><p><strong>Overall: 78% complete (101/129 tasks)</strong></p><pre><code>███████████████████████░░░░░░░</code></pre><p></p><p><strong>By category:</strong></p><p>Documents &amp; drafts:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 10/10</p><p>Code changes:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 69% <code>████████████████░░░░░░░░</code> 11/16</p><p>Decision docs:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 3/3</p><p>Bug fixes:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 1/1</p><p>Awaiting your decisions: &nbsp;0% <code>░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░</code> 0/5</p><p>External / user-only:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 0% <code>░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░</code> 0/9</p><p>Post-launch (deferred):&nbsp;&nbsp; 0% <code>░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░</code> 0/9</p><p></p><p><strong>Shipped 2026-05-17:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Auth Phase 1 — DONE &amp; verified.</strong> Tier model + env-gated Clerk auth layer; dormant until keys are set.</p></li><li><p><strong>Auth Phase 2 — DONE.</strong> Billing scaffolding: env-gated Stripe + RevenueCat, dormant until keys. (Phase 3 = tier enforcement #33 still pending.)</p></li><li><p><strong>LIVE BOOKS — BUILT &amp; shipped.</strong> Generalized transform engine; documented in all 4 places; core surface runtime-proven by a new automated test (dialog/scope/preview/auto-apply-off/merge-overwrite all pass). Residual: live AI refresh round-trip + post-refresh diff cards not yet automation-covered (medium follow-up #57).</p></li><li><p><strong>Language translation (#52) de-risked</strong> — LIVE BOOKS shipped the shared transform engine it plugs into.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Gemini 3.5 Flash switch (#49) — DONE.</strong> Google I/O 2026 (2026-05-19) shipped Gemini 3.5 Flash, not a &quot;Gemini 4&quot;. The app-wide default now points at gemini-3.5-flash; 2.5 Flash stays registered as a one-line rollback. Soft launch-copy variant finalized in docs/launch/gemini-3.5-flash.md; the BYOK setup guide now notes Google&#39;s ~55-day free-tier data retention. Remaining: publish marketing copy + deploy.</p><p><strong>Infra:</strong> project relocated out of iCloud to ~/Developer/IdiamPro (machine-load problem permanently resolved); git auth moved to macOS Keychain.</p><p><strong>TEST EVERYTHING 2026-05-17: 38/38 on clean runs</strong> (electron 8/8, gemma4 6/6, mcp 24/24); relocated repo validated healthy.</p>", "type": "root", "parentId": null, "childrenIds": ["lp-completed", "lp-decisions", "lp-external", "lp-next", "lp-deferred"], "prefix": ""}, "lp-completed": {"id": "lp-completed", "name": "Completed (22)", "parentId": "lp-root", "childrenIds": [], "type": "chapter", "content": "<p><strong>Auth Phase 1 — DONE &amp; verified (#32).</strong> Tier model + env-gated Clerk auth layer. No-ops with no keys set; zero runtime cost until activated.</p><p><strong>Auth Phase 2 — DONE.</strong> Billing scaffolding: env-gated Stripe + RevenueCat, dormant until keys. Phase 3 (tier enforcement #33) still pending.</p><p><strong>LIVE BOOKS — BUILT &amp; shipped (#2).</strong> Generalized transform engine; documented in User Guide, Help Chat context, Help Chat API context, and How It Works outline. Core surface runtime-proven by a new automated Playwright test (#54): dialog, scope selection, preview, auto-apply-off, and merge-vs-overwrite all pass. Residual (medium follow-up #57): live AI refresh round-trip + post-refresh per-node diff cards not yet automation-covered.</p><p><strong>LIVE BOOKS automated test (#54) — DONE.</strong> Added to the Playwright suite; core surface verified runtime-working.</p><p><strong>Gemini 3.5 Flash switch — DONE (#49).</strong> Google I/O 2026 (2026-05-19) shipped Gemini 3.5 Flash, not a &quot;Gemini 4&quot;. The Gemini model registry is the single source of truth; the app-wide default now points at gemini-3.5-flash, with 2.5 Flash kept as a one-line rollback. Launch copy finalized in the soft variant (docs/launch/gemini-3.5-flash.md); the BYOK setup guide notes Google&#39;s ~55-day free-tier data retention.</p><p>Website updated &amp; live — stale March launch date removed, concrete role examples added.</p><p>Sentry crash reporting integrated across web, Electron, edge runtime. Free-tier safe. Needs a DSN from you to start collecting reports.</p><p>Accessibility audit (WCAG 2.1 AA). About 23 fixes applied — icon-only buttons got aria-labels, the outline now has proper ARIA tree semantics. Build clean.</p><p>Terms of Service draft. Marked DRAFT — needs lawyer review and a jurisdiction choice.</p><p>Refund Policy + dispute handling SOP. 14-day window, 3-day SLA, BYOK carve-outs documented.</p><p>App Privacy Nutrition Labels recommendation. Row-by-row answers ready for App Store Connect.</p><p>AI Consent reviewer documentation. Step-by-step for Apple App Review.</p><p>Incident Response + Backup/DR playbook. SEV ladder, scenario runbooks, post-mortem template.</p><p>Email deliverability setup guide. Resend + Google Workspace recommended. SPF/DKIM/DMARC steps.</p><p>Mac App Store decision: DMG-only for v1 (sandboxing would break Ollama, file access, MCP).</p><p>Sign in with Apple audit: not required — no auth exists today.</p><p>Launch announcement drafts: Product Hunt, Hacker News, Twitter, LinkedIn.</p><p>Beta tester + influencer outreach templates. Nick Milo (Linking Your Thinking) is the top target.</p><p>Knowledge Chat &quot;All Outlines&quot; test bug fixed. 38/38 tests passing.</p><p><strong>Auth provider — DECIDED 2026-05-26: Clerk.</strong> Lowest-friction path; the Phase-1 auth scaffolding already shipped is built around Clerk. Supports Sign In With Apple natively (required if we ever offer any third-party login on iOS per App Store guideline 4.8).</p><p><strong>Billing architecture — DECIDED 2026-05-26: RevenueCat orchestrating Apple IAP for v1; Stripe later via RevenueCat dashboard.</strong> iOS app legally must use Apple IAP for digital subscriptions (App Store 3.1.1). RevenueCat sits on top of Apple IAP and gives the app one entitlement API; free up to $2,500 MTR. When web payments matter later, Stripe plugs into RevenueCat without any app-code change — same entitlement API. Apple takes 30%/15% (Small Business Program); Stripe ~3% later.</p><p><strong>Tagline DECIDED 2026-05-26: \"The Premier Idea Developer.\"</strong> Headline + sub-headline + descriptive paragraph locked in. Sub-headline: \"Any idea. Any team, anywhere. Any language. AI at every step.\" A dedicated \"Built for globally distributed teams\" section sits directly under the hero with a concrete scene (Boston + Shanghai + São Paulo team collaborating in their native languages). Replaces the prior \"Build Your Second Brain\" hero. Both src/app/page.tsx and src/app/marketing/page.tsx updated to match.</p><p><strong>Pricing DECIDED 2026-05-26: 3-tier accessible structure.</strong> Free (BYOK; bring your own AI key for unlimited use), Student $4.99/mo (50% off, requires verification, 200 AI generations/month), Pro $9.99/mo or $89/year (save 25%; 1,000 AI generations/month, podcast + image generation, priority support). Replaces the prior 4-tier structure that had the $49.99 \"Academic\" tier (which was the opposite of accessible for students). Premium $29.99 tier removed for v1 — can be added back later as an upsell if telemetry shows demand. Marketing copy on both src/app/page.tsx and src/app/marketing/page.tsx updated.</p>", "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "1"}, "lp-decisions": {"id": "lp-decisions", "name": "Waiting on your decisions (2)", "parentId": "lp-root", "childrenIds": [], "type": "chapter", "content": "<p><strong>Support email confirmation</strong> — support@2ndbrainware.com or something else? Affects refund policy, incident response, customer support setup.</p><p><strong>Status page vendor + Postgres provider + Lawyer-on-call + Legal jurisdiction</strong> — Needed to finalize the docs already drafted.</p>", "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "2"}, "lp-external": {"id": "lp-external", "name": "Waiting on external / user-only (9)", "parentId": "lp-root", "childrenIds": [], "type": "chapter", "content": "<p>Apple Developer cert ($99/yr) — verify account active, configure Team ID</p><p>Privacy Policy lawyer review — already drafted at /privacy, needs sign-off</p><p>Sentry DSN — create free Sentry account, paste DSN into Vercel env vars</p><p>Custom domain DNS — point secondbrainware.com to Vercel</p><p>iOS TestFlight upload — needs your office / fast internet</p><p>Real-device test pass — Mac primary, then iPhone/iPad verification</p><p>Business infrastructure — LLC, bank account, Stripe Atlas entity, Google Play developer account</p><p>4 enterprise API responses — passive monitoring of inboxes</p><p>Customer support tooling pick — email-only, Help Scout, Front, etc.</p>", "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "3"}, "lp-next": {"id": "lp-next", "name": "Next to tackle (P0 code work)", "parentId": "lp-root", "childrenIds": [], "type": "chapter", "content": "<p><strong>Unblocked 2026-05-26 by today's decisions:</strong> #32 (user authentication via Clerk) and #15 (subscription billing backend via RevenueCat) can now proceed. Auth Phase 3 / tier enforcement (#33) still needs Clerk + RevenueCat keys to go live — those are part of the deploy step, not a code change.</p><p><strong>Google I/O 2026 — DONE (2026-05-19 keynote).</strong> Google shipped Gemini 3.5 Flash; the app default was switched to gemini-3.5-flash by hand (no &quot;gemini-4-*&quot; ids existed, so the launch script&#39;s auto-discovery found nothing). Soft launch-copy variant finalized. Remaining follow-through: publish the marketing copy and deploy.</p><p></p><p><strong>Gemini 3.5 Flash switch (#49) — DONE.</strong> Completed 2026-05-21 — see the Completed list. Default switched to gemini-3.5-flash; launch copy ready to publish.</p><p></p><p><strong>After the keynote — ranked by what unblocks the most other work:</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>1. Feature gating + tier enforcement (#33) = Auth Phase 3.</strong> Auth Phase 1 (foundation) and Phase 2 (billing scaffolding) are DONE; this is the remaining piece to actually gate paid features. Still needs provider keys to go live.</p><p><strong>2. BYOK API key entry UI + secure storage (#34)</strong> — auth foundation now exists; this is unblocked.</p><p><strong>3. LIVE BOOKS live-refresh verification (#57, medium)</strong> — automate the live AI refresh round-trip + post-refresh per-node diff cards.</p><p><strong>4. Language translation (#52, HIGH)</strong> — now de-risked: LIVE BOOKS shipped the shared transform engine it plugs into.</p><p><strong>5. Launch metrics dashboard (#47)</strong> — pick 5-7 numbers for launch week (signups, activation, retention, conversion).</p><p><strong>6. Onboarding email sequence (#46)</strong> — welcome + 3-5 drip emails after signup.</p><p><strong>7. Web payment / Stripe (#22)</strong> — billing scaffolding now in place; needs keys + tier enforcement.</p><p></p><p>Low-priority cleanup: test-screenshots relocation artifact (#55), flaky MCP search test (#56), ~59 pre-existing TS errors (#51).</p>", "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "4"}, "lp-deferred": {"id": "lp-deferred", "name": "Post-launch / deferred (9)", "parentId": "lp-root", "childrenIds": [], "type": "chapter", "content": "<p>Not launch-blocking. These ship after the Apple version is live and monetized.</p><p></p><p>LIVE BOOKS — design + implementation (the 6 open design questions remain)</p><p>Android Capacitor scaffolding</p><p>Windows distributed build</p><p>Linux distributed build</p><p>MCP Server Phase 2 (free CRUD tools)</p><p>MCP Server Phase 3 (premium AI/ingest tools)</p><p>MCP Server Phase 4 (dual-licensing strategy)</p><p>MCP Server Test 8 (Claude Desktop end-to-end)</p><p>Collaboration / Group features — entire Group outline is design-only</p><p>Build managed API proxy tier (v2 of monetization, after first enterprise agreement)</p><p>iOS multi-select audit (refinement)</p>", "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "5"}}, "isGuide": false, "_fileName": "IdiamPro - Launch Progress.idm", "_isLazyLoaded": false}